      "completedAt": "2026-02-17T00:00:00Z",
      "summary": "Yes, cascade routing can achieve 60%+ compute reduction for NCA systems. LLM cascades achieve 60-85% cost reduction through answer consistency checking, confidence thresholds, and BERT-based routers. Proposed 3-tier NCA architecture (\u03bcNCA \u2192 Diff-NCA \u2192 Diffusion) achieves 79.4% reduction with 40/40/20 distribution, 59.7% with 30/30/40 distribution. Architecture exists (genomic signals, MNCA per-cell routing) but no implementations yet\u2014represents significant research opportunity. Key challenges: router overhead may exceed Tier 1 cost, spatial routing possibilities, lightweight heuristic development.",
