    {
      "id": "rq-1770915400000-nca-load-balancing",
      "topic": "Load balancing in spatial MoE systems - do NCAs need auxiliary losses like LLM MoE models to prevent expert collapse?",
      "source": "Research follow-up from NCA model zoos study",
      "addedBy": "research-agent",
      "addedAt": "2026-02-14T23:45:00Z",
      "priority": 6,
      "tags": [
        "neural-networks",
        "mixture-of-experts",
        "load-balancing",
        "spatial-routing",
        "nca"
      ],
      "completedAt": "2026-02-15T12:00:00Z",
      "summary": "NCAs operate in fundamentally different paradigm than token-based MoE. Standard NCAs use homogeneous rules achieving heterogeneity through emergence. Spatial MoE-NCAs (MNCA, PD-NCA) implement per-cell routing but address collapse through competitive dynamics, environmental pressure, and stochastic mechanisms rather than auxiliary losses. Key insight: spatial correlation and task objectives determine whether load balancing is needed\u2014biological tasks often don't need it; computational tasks may benefit.",
      "sources": [
        "https://openreview.net/forum?id=y1iU5czYpE",
        "https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.15664",
        "https://arxiv.org/html/2506.20486",
