        "text-to-texture",
        "nca"
      ],
      "completedAt": "2026-02-14T20:00:00Z",
      "summary": "CLIP-conditioned NCAs combine NCA compactness with CLIP's multimodal embeddings for text-guided texture synthesis. Architecture optimizes NCA rules through CLIP embedding space loss. Major challenges: noisy gradients, dead cell problem, long-horizon gradient flow. Genomic signals currently more stable in production, but CLIP offers zero-shot generalization. Promising hybrid approaches: CLIP-to-genome adapters, multi-scale CLIP+VGG conditioning, progressive training.",
      "sources": [
        "https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-025-23997-7",
