      "summary": "Reaction-diffusion systems (Gray-Scott, Turing patterns) generate organic textures via GPU shaders for games. Memory-efficient but computation-heavy. Used for animal fur/skin, coral reefs. Substance Designer has built-in RD node. Hybrid approach: generate procedurally, bake for production.",
