    {
      "id": "rq-1739950000000-hybrid-genomic-latent",
      "topic": "Hybrid genomic-latent NCAs: Can genomic signals operate in latent space for extreme compression + multi-texture capability?",
      "source": "Research follow-up from controllable NCA study",
      "addedBy": "research-agent",
      "addedAt": "2026-02-18T09:00:00Z",
      "priority": 7,
      "tags": [
        "neural-networks",
        "genomic-signals",
        "latent-space",
        "multi-texture",
        "nca"
      ],
      "completedAt": "2026-02-18T15:50:00Z",
      "summary": "Hybrid genomic-latent NCAs combine multi-texture genomic encoding (8+ textures, 1,500-10,000 params) with latent space compression (94% memory reduction, 16\u00d7 input capacity). No implementations exist yet, but three proven paradigms provide building blocks: LNCA for latent operation, genomic signals for multi-texture capability, VNCA for probabilistic frameworks. Key challenge: preserving genomic identity through aggressive compression\u2014solvable via skip connections, hierarchical separation, or variational conditioning. Potential impact: <20k params for 16+ textures at high resolution with real-time performance.",
      "sources": [
        "https://arxiv.org/html/2403.15525",
        "https://arxiv.org/html/2506.22899v2",
        "https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.22899",
        "https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-025-23997-7",
        "https://arxiv.org/html/2407.05991v2",
        "https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2201.12360",
        "https://arxiv.org/abs/2201.12360",
        "https://openreview.net/forum?id=7fFO4cMBx_9",
